\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Daily Standup Meeting 25: Dashboard Polish & Visual Feedback\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Date:
\f1\b0  3 April 2026 | 
\f0\b Sprint:
\f1\b0  2 | 
\f0\b Attendance:
\f1\b0  All Present\
The meeting today focused on the final "aesthetic and functional" polish of the system dashboard. 
\f0\b Brent Li (Developer)
\f1\b0  demonstrated the updated dashboard, which now includes the "calm and relaxing" colour palette across all screens, from the login page to the breakdown charts. He explained that the soft blue gradients were specifically chosen to match the corporate branding of our roadside company partner. 
\f0\b Hoang Nguyen (Developer)
\f1\b0  added that he had integrated a real-time "status indicator" that pulses softly when the Binary Search Tree (BST) is being traversed for a search. This visual feedback ensures the user knows the system is working without being jarring. He also confirmed that the custom chart drawing logic now handles empty data sets gracefully, showing a "No Active Breakdowns" message in a clean, professional font rather than a blank screen.\

\f0\b Shrayesh Lawaju (Tester)
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b Zion James-Simpson (Secretary)
\f1\b0  performed a final walkthrough of the dashboard\'92s navigation. Shrayesh confirmed that the "Dashboard View" and the "Analytical View" (where the charts live) are perfectly synchronised. He noted that the search results now highlight the relevant node in the BST data set using a subtle glow effect, which makes the "usable" nature of the software stand out for the markers. Zion began drafting the "User Interface Design" section of the report, specifically focusing on how the dashboard serves as a functional tool for a recovery dispatcher. 
\f0\b Avisha Garusingha (Team Leader)
\f1\b0  confirmed that the project is now visually complete, and the team will begin recording the demonstration video tomorrow morning.\
