\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 Daily Standup Meeting 26: Video Scripting & Dashboard Walkthrough\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Date:
\f1\b0  4 April 2026 | 
\f0\b Sprint:
\f1\b0  2 | 
\f0\b Attendance:
\f1\b0  All Present\
Today\'92s session was dedicated entirely to the 6-minute demonstration video. 
\f0\b Avisha Garusingha (Team Leader)
\f1\b0  presented a storyboard that highlights the project\'92s unique selling points: the custom BST, the roadside company partnership, and the professional dashboard. 
\f0\b Brent Li (Developer)
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b Hoang Nguyen (Developer)
\f1\b0  worked on a "demo dataset" to ensure the charts show a diverse range of breakdown types during the recording. Brent suggested that the video should specifically show the transition from the "calm" dashboard view to the underlying source code to prove the "No STL" constraint was met. Hoang added that they must narrate the code walkthrough by explaining how the recursive BST search updates the dashboard UI in real-time.\

\f0\b Zion James-Simpson (Secretary)
\f1\b0  reviewed the script to ensure the terminology matches the technical report. He emphasised that the video should explicitly mention the partnership with the roadside company to contextualise why we chose such a specific UI design. 
\f0\b Shrayesh Lawaju (Tester)
\f1\b0  conducted a final system "smoke test" before the cameras started rolling to ensure no last-minute bugs occurred during the live demonstration. He also checked the audio quality of the team's microphones, as the brief states that the demonstration must be clearly explained to receive marks. The team agreed to film the "System in Action" segment first, followed by the "Code Explanation" segment, to ensure the 6-minute limit is respected.\
